This Satire is, as will be seen from the above analysis, on the power of conscience and its revenge. Juvenal unites his teachings on revenge with the advice tendered to his friend Calvinus.

It has been imitated by Oldham in a powerful composition beginning

‘There is not one bad act which men commit

But carries this ill sting along with it,' etc. The philosophy is expressed in ‘otherio‘- ’ ‘To mourn a mischief which is past and gone ls the next way to draw new mischief on.‘
